p: Selina-6-en-4-ol (bicyclic sesquiterpenoid) was 0.23 to 1.6% in the EO of wild hemp, n.d. to 1.8% in the EO of the registered cultivars, and 1.1 to 2.8% in the EO of the breeding lines ( Supplementary Tables S1â€“S3). Its concentration was statistically highest in the EO of cv. Dioica and lower in the EOs of cvs. Bacalmas and Spic ( Table 2).
